summary: So I think we can infer that after their argument in 1862 Crowley and Aziraphale hadn’t spoken to each other until the showdown...
body: So I think we can infer that after their argument in 1862 Crowley and Aziraphale hadn’t spoken to each other until the showdown in the church in 1941. Which now begs the question how did Crowley know Aziraphale was going to get ambushed by those Nazis and how was he there at the perfect time to save him? I thought maybe they could just sense each other but that still wouldn’t explain how he knew Azira was gonna be in danger. The only explanation I can come up with is despite them “breaking up” Crowley still kept tabs on Aziraphale to make sure he was okay because even though they weren’t on good terms he was still concerned about the angel’s well being. That’s love.
